Must Reads

     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html]Scott Meyers' Advice to
       Prospective Book Authors
     * [http://www.fasterj.com/articles/bookwriting.shtml]Writing A
       Technical Book: Is It Worthwhile?

Book Proposals

     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130809065323/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch02.html]The Proposal (O'Reilly: So You Want to Write a
       Book?)
     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#bookProposal]Scott
       Meyers' Advice on Preparing a Book Proposal
     * [http://www.informit.com/about/write_for_us.aspx]Write for Us
       (Pearson Education)
     * [http://www.quepublishing.com/promotions/write-for-us-drafting-a-pr
       oposal-137677]Drafting a Proposal (Que Publishing)
     * [http://www.quepublishing.com/promotions/write-for-us-anatomy-of-a-
       toc-137678]Anatomy of a TOC (Que Publishing)
     * [https://pragprog.com/write-for-us/proposal-guidelines]Proposal
       Guidelines (The Pragmatic Programmers)

Contracts

     * [http://www.writersdigest.com/online-editor/book-contract-whats-neg
       otiable-and-whats-not]Book Contract: What's Negotiable and What's
       Not
     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#contracts]Scott Meyers'
       Advice on Contracts
     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130704110948/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch03.html]The Contract (O'Reilly: So You Want to Write a
       Book?)
     * [https://web.archive.org/web/20161010102603/http://www.apress.com/f
       iles/Apress_Contract.pdf]Apress Standard Contract
     * [https://www.nostarch.com/download/nspagreement.pdf]No Starch Press
       Standard Contract

Royalties, Advances, and Other Money Stuff

     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#moneyStuff]Scott Meyers
       on Royalties, Advances, and Other Money Stuff
     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130704110948/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch03.html#royadv]Royalties and Advances (O'Reilly: So You
       Want to Write a Book?)
     * [http://www.fasterj.com/articles/bookwriting.shtml]Writing A
       Technical Book: Is It Worthwhile? - The benefits for writing a
       technical book, and the basics of how book advances work.
     * [http://www.writersdigest.com/online-editor/how-book-advances-work-
       a-simple-explanation-for-writers]How Book Advances Work - A Simple
       Explanation for Writers
     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130704110948/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch03.html#advance]Typical O'Reilly Advance Structure

Editors

     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#publishersAndEditors]Sco
       tt Meyers on the Importance of a Good Editor
     * [http://www.quepublishing.com/promotions/write-for-us-the-editing-p
       rocess-137679]The Editing Process and Editor Types (Que Publishing)
     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130710213743/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch04.html]Writing and Editing (O'Reilly: So You Want to
       Write a Book?)

Publishers

     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#findingAPublisher]Scott
       Meyers' Advice on Finding a Publisher

Marketing

     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20130711002825/http://oreilly.com/oreil
       ly/author/ch06.html]Marketing Your Book (O'Reilly: So You Want to
       Write a Book?)

Misc.

     * [http://www.aristeia.com/authorAdvice.html#schedule]Scott Meyers on
       Advance Sales, and How They Are Impacted by The Delivery Schedule

List of Publishers

     * [http://www.oreilly.com/work-with-us.html]O'Reilly
     * [http://www.apress.com/write-for-us/]Apress
     * [https://write-with-us.pragprog.com/]The Pragmatic Programmers
     * [http://authors.packtpub.com/]Packt Publishing
     * [http://www.informit.com/about/write_for_us.aspx]Pearson (parent
       company for Addison-Wesley, Prentice Hall Professional, Que, Sams,
       and more)
     * [http://www.quepublishing.com/about/write_for_us.aspx]Que
       Publishing
     * [https://www.manning.com/write-for-us]Manning Publications
     * [http://www.wrox.com/WileyCDA/Section/id-105073.html]Wrox
     * [https://www.nostarch.com/writeforus.htm]No Starch Press

Self Publishing

     * [https://medium.com/@davetron5000/self-vs-professional-publishing-c
       3397bd7defd#.lrfhasuo5]Self vs Professional Publishing - The pros
       and cons of each, plus a look at many of the options available for
       self publishing.

Writing Workflows and Tooling

     * [https://medium.com/@chacon/living-the-future-of-technical-writing-
       2f368bd0a272#.8x6g1wxjb]Living the Future of Technical Writing -
       Scott Chacon shares his workflow and tools for writing "Pro Git" in
       Asciidoc.

Personal Experiences, Post Mortems and Campfire Stories

     * [https://medium.com/@brindelle/writing-a-programming-book-faqs-afte
       r-writing-learning-react-native-8a5ea8ce04e#.e85mhxolh]Writing a
       Programming Book: FAQs after Writing Learning React Native
     * [http://blog.codinghorror.com/do-not-buy-this-book/]Do Not Buy This
       Book - Jeff Atwood's warning to potential writers.
     * [http://www.adamtornhill.com/articles/writingbook/writingtechbook.h
       tm]Writing a Technical Book: Motivation, Publishing and how to stay
       focused without ruining your Life - Adam Tornhill shares experience
       gained writing his three books (two of them self published).
     * [http://www.voidspace.org.uk/python/articles/technical-writing.shtm
       l]Writing a Technical Book - Michael Foord shares his experience
       publishing with Apress.
     * [http://www.philosophicalgeek.com/2014/11/10/tips-for-writing-a-pro
       gramming-book/]Tips for Writing a Programming Book

